      "description": "CFD-predicted normalised index of hemolysis compared against in vitro hemolysis measurements from five independent pump specimens tested at matched operating conditions. Relative hemolysis index RH computed for each specimen pair. Inherent variability in biological blood samples and inter-specimen manufacturing tolerances assessed qualitatively by the assessment team; no structured probabilistic UQ model was constructed for this result. The spread across specimens was noted in narrative review but not propagated into a formal uncertainty bound."
